fs module
1) readdirsync - read data from directory synchronously
2) readefilesync - read data from file synchronously
3) statSync - get meta data of the file- 
statSync returns a Stats object containing details such as:
File size
Creation time
Modification time
Whether it's a file or directory

path module
1) join - joins path segments togethor
2) resolve - converts a sequence of paths into an absolute path.
3) basename - get the last part of path( ex- /home/user/file.txt , output = file.txt)
4) extname - returns the file extension
